09/07/2004
BAGHDAD, Iraq -- The driver of a Turkish lorry and a passenger traveling with him have been killed in Iraq, NTV reported Friday (9 July). The lorry was part of a convoy carrying supplies along the Samarra-Balad road, a main route 125km north of Baghdad, when it was attacked by unidentified rebel forces. When the lorry flipped over, rebels shot the driver and passenger dead. Several Turkish citizens were recently kidnapped and then released in Iraq. (NTV - 09/07/04)
